<p>Adhesions can occur anywhere in the body. But they often form after surgery on the abdomen. Almost everyone who has surgery on the abdomen gets adhesions. Some adhesions don't cause any problems. But when they partly or completely <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/intestinalobstruction.html">block the intestines</a>, they cause symptoms such as:</p>
