<p>Adhesions can sometimes cause <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/femaleinfertility.html">infertility in women</a> by preventing fertilized eggs from reaching the uterus.</p>
<p>No tests are available to detect adhesions. Doctors usually find them during surgery to diagnose other problems.</p>
<p>Some adhesions go away by themselves. If they partly block your intestines, a diet low in fiber can allow food to move easily through the affected area. If you have a complete intestinal obstruction, it is life-threatening. You should get immediate medical attention and may need surgery. </p>
