<p>A cataract can occur in either or both eyes. It cannot spread from one eye to the other. Common symptoms are:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Blurry vision</li>
	<li>Colors that seem faded</li>
	<li>Glare - headlights, lamps or sunlight may seem too bright. You may also see a halo around lights.</li>
