<p>A <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/lab-tests/cholesterol-levels/">blood test</a> called a lipoprotein or lipid panel can measure your cholesterol levels. Before the test, you'll need to <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/lab-tests/fasting-for-a-blood-test/">fast</a> (not eat or drink anything but water) for 9 to 12 hours. The test gives information about your:</p>
