ent Handouts Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Treatments and Therapies Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Diagnosis and Tests National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases NIH Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Specifics National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases NIH Genetics National Library of Medicine NIH Find an Expert National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases NIH Treatments and Therapies National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases NIH Treatments and Therapies National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health NIH Journal Articles Patient Handouts Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Encyclopedia Medical Encyclopedia Reference Desk National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases NIH Colon polyps <p>A polyp is an extra piece of tissue that grows inside your body. Colonic polyps grow in the large intestine, or colon. Most polyps are not dangerous. However, some polyps may turn into cancer or already be cancer. To be safe, doctors remove polyps and test them. Polyps can be removed when a doctor examines the inside of the large intestine during a <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/colonoscopy.html">colonoscopy</a>.</p>
